		<form>
			<ul id="options">
				<li>
					<label for="name">App Name</label>
					<input id="name" type="text" required>
				</li>
				<li>
					<label for="desc">Description</label>
					<textarea id="desc"></textarea>
				</li>
				<li>
					<label for="url">URL</label>
					<input id="url" type="text" required>
				</li>
				<li>
					<label for="icon">Icon</label>
					<aside>(Must be a .png file, should be 128×128)</aside>
					<!-- TODO: default to touch icon -->
					<input id="icon" type="file" accept="image/png" required>
					<img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAID/AMDAwAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==" alt="Image preview...">
				</li>
				<li>
					<label for="windowHeight">Default window size</label>
					<aside>(width × height)</aside><br>
					<input id="windowWidth" value="800" min="100" type="number" required> ×
					<input id="windowHeight" value="560" min="100" type="number" required>
				</li>
				<li class="mini">
					<label for="saveState">Keep browser data when closed</label>
					<input id="saveState" type="checkbox" checked>
				</li>
			</ul>

			<button type="submit" class="is-disabled">Generate</button> <!-- using a class to enable visual form validation -->
		</form>
	</main>

	<aside id="instructions">
		<h2>Installation instructions</h2>
		<ol>
			<li>Extract the zip file</li>
			<li>Go to <a href="chrome://extensions" class="hint--top" data-hint="You can't click this link, you'll have to copy-paste it manually :/">chrome://extensions/</a></li>
			<li>Make sure the <i>Developer Mode</i> checkbox is checked</li>
			<li>Click Load unpacked extension…</li>
			<li>Select the extracted folder and click OK</li>
		</ol>
		<br>
		<p>You can now go to <a href="chrome://apps" class="hint--top" data-hint="You can't click this link, you'll have to copy-paste it manually :/">chrome://apps</a> to launch your newly created app.</p>
	</aside>

	<footer>
		<p>Everything happens in the browser, no data is sent to the server.</p>
		<p>Please note that any browser extensions installed won't affect the app, e.g. JS will still work if NoScript is installed.</p>
		<br>
		<p>
		<iframe src="https://ghbtns.com/github-btn.html?user=matthias-vogt&repo=website-to-chrome-app&type=fork&count=true&size=large" frameborder="0" scrolling="0" width="158px" height="30px"></iframe>
